    "created_at": "2014-12-10T20:55:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-12-10T20:55:30Z",
    "body": "Maybe, I wouldn't know. I think generally it would not be unreasonable to require people who wish to port rustc to a new platform to have access to at least one of the currently supported targets, especially since it is so easy to run linux on a VM. And when we reach Rust 1.0, perhaps it would be possible to make sure the compiler uses only stable features, and then porting the compiler to a platform once should ensure it can compile any future version of the compiler.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
