    "body": "PNaCl provides a portable bytecode and `rustc` is able to target it... but it's not going to run without someone working to expose everything it needs in the execution environment. At that point you'll have written a portable OS API usable for running lots of existing software.\n\nIf someone really wants to do that then nothing is stopping them - but it doesn't belong in this bug tracker. It's not at all in the scope of the project and there's no advantage to doing it in this repository. It doesn't seem very Rust-specific either.\n",
