    "updated_at": "2017-12-18T08:16:25Z",
    "body": "The rust compiler used to be implemented in Ocaml. You are free to bootstrap all the way from that version to master if Ken scares you, unless you believe the Ocaml tools have code hidden inside them to detect whether they are compiling a Rust compiler, but at that point you're probably excessively paranoid.\r\n\r\nRegardless, there is a project to implement a Rust compiler in c++, so soon (tm) you will be able to bootstrap that way as well. ",
